Welcome to SilverStack SonarQube Lab! 🔍

SonarQube is running internally at http://localhost:<SONARQUBE_PORT>
Nginx reverse proxy is listening on port 80 (internal)
PostgreSQL database is running on port 5432 (internal)

Pre-installed tools:
- curl, socat         Networking toolkit
- arkade              Installer for additional tools
- cloudflared         Cloudflare Tunnel for public access
- java 21             Modern LTS Java runtime
- postgresql 18       Production-grade database

Default SonarQube credentials:
  Username: admin
  Password: admin 

To expose SonarQube publicly via Cloudflare Tunnel:

  1. one.dash.cloudflare.com → Zero Trust → Networks → Connectors
  2. Create tunnel → name it (e.g. sonarqube-lab) → choose Cloudflared
  3. Copy & run the install command shown:
       sudo cloudflared service install <token>
  4. Route Traffic → Add public hostname:
       Subdomain: sonar   Domain: yourdomain.com
       Service:   HTTP    URL:    localhost:<SONARQUBE_PORT>
  5. SonarQube is now live at https://sonar.yourdomain.com

Quick commands:
  sonar-status  sonar-logs  sonar-restart  sonar-start  sonar-stop
  pg-status     pg-logs     pg-restart
  nginx-status  nginx-logs  nginx-reload
